    public enum BmcProperties

    Enum to encapsulate all of the configuration options available to users.

      • MULTIPART_ALLOWED

        public static final BmcProperties MULTIPART_ALLOWED
        (boolean, optional) Flag for whether or not multi-part uploads are allowed at all. See BmcConstants.MULTIPART_ALLOWED_KEY for config key name. Default true.

      • MULTIPART_NUM_UPLOAD_THREADS

        public static final BmcProperties MULTIPART_NUM_UPLOAD_THREADS
        (int, optional) The number of threads to use for parallel multi-part uploads. Note, any value <= 0 is interpreted as using the default Java SDK value. A value of 1 means do not use parallel uploads (you can still use multi-part if the "allowed" property is true, but each part will be uploaded serially. This will be one thread per upload). Otherwise, this represents the total number of threads shared amongst all requests (not per request). See BmcConstants.MULTIPART_NUM_UPLOAD_THREADS_KEY for config key name.

      • MULTIPART_MIN_SIZE_OF_OBJECT_IN_MB

        public static final BmcProperties MULTIPART_MIN_SIZE_OF_OBJECT_IN_MB
        (int, optional) The minimum size, in mebibytes, an object must be before its eligible for multi-part uploads. Note, any value <= 0 is interpreted as using the default Java SDK value. See BmcConstants.MULTIPART_MIN_SIZE_OF_OBJECT_IN_MB_KEY for config key name.

      • MULTIPART_MIN_PART_SIZE_IN_MB

        @Deprecated
public static final BmcProperties MULTIPART_MIN_PART_SIZE_IN_MB
        Deprecated. use MULTIPART_PART_SIZE_IN_MB instead
        (int, optional) The minimum size, in mebibytes, each part should be uploaded as. Note, any value <= 0 is interpreted as using the default Java SDK value. See BmcConstants.MULTIPART_MIN_PART_SIZE_IN_MB_KEY for config key name.

      • MULTIPART_PART_SIZE_IN_MB

        public static final BmcProperties MULTIPART_PART_SIZE_IN_MB
        (int, optional) The part size, in mebibytes that each part should be uploaded as. Note, any value <= 0 is interpreted as using the default Java SDK value. See BmcConstants.MULTIPART_PART_SIZE_IN_MB_KEY for config key name.

      • HTTP_PROXY_URI

        public static final BmcProperties HTTP_PROXY_URI
        (string, optional) The HTTP proxy URI if using a proxy to connect to Object Storage Service. If configured, then an ObjectStorageClient will be configured to use the ApacheConnector provider add-on in order to configure the proxy for the client. Note: This buffers all requests (uploads) and can impact memory utiliziation. See BmcConstants.HTTP_PROXY_URI_KEY for the config key name.

      • HTTP_PROXY_USERNAME

        public static final BmcProperties HTTP_PROXY_USERNAME
        (string, optional) The username to use for the configured HTTP proxy via HTTP_PROXY_URI. See BmcConstants.HTTP_PROXY_USERNAME_KEY for the config key name.

      • HTTP_PROXY_PASSWORD

        public static final BmcProperties HTTP_PROXY_PASSWORD
        (string, optional) The password to use with the associated HTTP_PROXY_USERNAME. See BmcConstants.HTTP_PROXY_PASSWORD_KEY for the config key name.

      • RETRY_TIMEOUT_IN_SECONDS

        public static final BmcProperties RETRY_TIMEOUT_IN_SECONDS
        (long, optional) The timeout to use for exponential delay retries for retryable service errors. This value is ignored if OBJECT_STORE_CLIENT_CLASS is specified. See BmcConstants.RETRY_TIMEOUT_IN_SECONDS_KEY for config key name. Default is 30.
